wwpQos410MIB.name: wwpQos410MIB
wwpQos410MIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpQos410MIB.description: The MIB module for the WWP QOS specific information.

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpQos410Table.name: wwpQos410Table
wwpQos410Table.description: A Table of QOS per vlan per port Entries.

wwpQos410Entry.name: wwpQos410Entry
wwpQos410Entry.description: The QOS per vlan per port Entry in the Table.

wwpQos410VlanId.name: wwpQos410VlanId
wwpQos410VlanId.description: Vlan ID for this instance of QOS. This Vlan Id should refer to the wwpVlanId in the WwpVlanEntry.

wwpQos410IngressPortId.name: wwpQos410IngressPortId
wwpQos410IngressPortId.description: Ingress Port ID for this instance of. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQos410EgressPortId.name: wwpQos410EgressPortId
wwpQos410EgressPortId.description: Egress Port ID for this instance of. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQos410MinRateLimit.name: wwpQos410MinRateLimit
wwpQos410MinRateLimit.description: Bandwidth guaranteed for this QOS entry, specified in 64Kb/s increments. The maximum value for this object is 8Gb/s, if this egress port is the lead port of a link aggregation group. The total of all QOS entries for this port cannot exceed the total bandwidth of the port or the set will fail.

wwpQos410MaxRateLimit.name: wwpQos410MaxRateLimit
wwpQos410MaxRateLimit.description: Bandwidth limit that cannot be exceeded by this QOS entry. The bandwidth is specified in 64Kb/s increments, with a maximum of 8Gb/s. The value specified cannot exceed the current bandwidth of the port. Values greater than 1 Gb/s can only be setup once a link agg group has been established.

wwpQos410QueueSize.name: wwpQos410QueueSize
wwpQos410QueueSize.description: The size of the queue for this QOS entry.

wwpQos410Weight.name: wwpQos410Weight
wwpQos410Weight.description: Value that is used to determine which QOS entries will receive the remaining bandwidth once Minimum Bandwidth requirements have been satisfied for all QOS entries. QOS entries with greater weight (smaller number) will receive a larger portion of this bandwidth.

wwpQos410RowStatus.name: wwpQos410RowStatus
wwpQos410RowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpQos410StatsTable.name: wwpQos410StatsTable
wwpQos410StatsTable.description: A Table of QOS Stats per vlan per ingress/egress port Entries.

wwpQos410StatsEntry.name: wwpQos410StatsEntry
wwpQos410StatsEntry.description: The QOS Stats per vlan per port Entry in the Table.

wwpQos410StatsVlanId.name: wwpQos410StatsVlanId
wwpQos410StatsVlanId.description: Vlan ID for this instance of QOS. This Vlan Id should refer to the wwpVlanId in the WwpVlanEntry.

wwpQos410StatsIngressPortId.name: wwpQos410StatsIngressPortId
wwpQos410StatsIngressPortId.description: Ingress Port ID for this instance of . Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQos410StatsEgressPortId.name: wwpQos410StatsEgressPortId
wwpQos410StatsEgressPortId.description: Egress Port ID for this instance of. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQos410StatsType.name: wwpQos410StatsType
wwpQos410StatsType.description: Determines which type of bytes to count, accepted bytes or discarded bytes for this QOS entry. The default will count accepted bytes.

wwpQos410RxBytesHi.name: wwpQos410RxBytesHi
wwpQos410RxBytesHi.description: The number of bytes received for this QOS Entry.This counter represents the upper 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpQos410RxBytesLo.name: wwpQos410RxBytesLo
wwpQos410RxBytesLo.description: The number of bytes received for this QOS Entry.This counter represents the lower 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpQos410PriToQMapTable.name: wwpQos410PriToQMapTable
wwpQos410PriToQMapTable.description: A Table of mapping of an RX-priority to a TX-queue.

wwpQos410PriToQMapEntry.name: wwpQos410PriToQMapEntry
wwpQos410PriToQMapEntry.description: The mapping Entry of an RX-priority to a TX-queue in the Table.

wwpQos410RxPriority.name: wwpQos410RxPriority
wwpQos410RxPriority.description: The RX-prioroty value for this entry.

wwpQos410TxPriQueue.name: wwpQos410TxPriQueue
wwpQos410TxPriQueue.description: The TX-priority-queue value for this entry.

wwpQos410PortTable.name: wwpQos410PortTable
wwpQos410PortTable.description: A Table of QOS per port Entries.

wwpQos410PortEntry.name: wwpQos410PortEntry
wwpQos410PortEntry.description: The QOS per port Entry in the Table.

wwpQos410PortIndex.name: wwpQos410PortIndex
wwpQos410PortIndex.description: Port ID for this instance of. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQos410PortProvisionedBW.name: wwpQos410PortProvisionedBW
wwpQos410PortProvisionedBW.description: Number of 64Kbps of bandwidth that is currently Provisioned for this port. This value is read-only and is updated each time a QOS entry is created for this port. If the port is a member of a Link Agg group and is not the lead port the value will be zero.

wwpQos410PortTotalBW.name: wwpQos410PortTotalBW
wwpQos410PortTotalBW.description: Number of 64Kbps of bandwidth that make up this port's total bandwidth. This value is read-only and is updated each time a QOS entry is created for this port. If the port is a member of a Link Agg group and this is not the lead port the value will be zero.

wwpQos410PortProvisionedNotifEnabled.name: wwpQos410PortProvisionedNotifEnabled
wwpQos410PortProvisionedNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpQos410PortOverProvisionedTrap and wwpQos410PortUnderProvisionedTrap. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpQos410PortOverProvisionedTrap.name: wwpQos410PortOverProvisionedTrap
wwpQos410PortOverProvisionedTrap.description: A wwpQos410PortOverProvisionedTrap notification is sent when the provisioned bandwidth exceeds the total bandwidth available for a port. This situation may also occur when changes in a link aggregation group (such as deleting a port from the group) decrease the total bandwidth or at the bootTime when the link aggregation groups are formed.

wwpQos410PortUnderProvisionedTrap.name: wwpQos410PortUnderProvisionedTrap
wwpQos410PortUnderProvisionedTrap.description: A wwpQos410PortUnderProvisionedTrap notification is sent when the previously over-provisioned situation is resolved for a port.
